title.narrative: VANUATU EMERGENCY RESPONSE

description.narrative: Vanuatu Emergency Response- Affected children in Vanuatu receive life-saving emergency interventions towards their recovery and return to normality, with strengthened resilience and capacities for mitigating the impact of future natural disasters., which contributes to Child Health, Child Protection And Emergencies, Cross-Sectoral Communication For Development, Cross-Sectoral Early Childhood Development, Cross-Sectoral Monitoring, Data And Situation Analyses, Cross-Sectoral Planning And Programme Reviews, Education In Emergencies, Equitable Access To Quality Education, Health And Emergencies, Nutrition And Emergencies, Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children, Sanitation, Supply And Logistics, Treatment Of Severe Acute Malnutrition, Unicef Capacity For Supply And Logistics, Wash And Emergencies, Water, Water Supply. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Children affected by emergencies in Pacific Islands receive support as per UNICEF CCCs

description.narrative: UNICEF, in partnership with the Government of Vanuatu and civil society organizations, supported life-saving humanitarian actions for the children of the Torres Group of Islands following Tropical Cyclone Donna and families and children during an emergency triggered by Monaro Volcano eruption that forced the evacuation of residents of Ambae Island | Status:Met | As-of Date:13/01/2018
